<TITLE> Babar sent to jail after 3 remands </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov13 (bdnews24.com)--Former BNP state minister for home Lutfozzaman Babar was sent to jail after he had been quizzed for 12 days under police custody in a case regarding the Aug 21, 2004 grenade attack. Babar was taken to Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court, Dhaka at 5pm. Magistrate Ferdous Ara, rejecting his bail petition, asked the authorities to arrange treatment for him in line with jail code. Additional SSP of CID police Abdul Kahhar Akhand, also investigation officer of the case, did not appeal further to remand the BNP leader for questioning. Babar, behind bars since March this year serving 17 years for an arms conviction, was shown arrested in the grenade attack case on Oct 26. The CID police remanded the BNP leader on Oct 29 in connection with the case after the Supreme Court put a seven-day halt on a High Court stay order regarding remanding Babar. A least 24 people including Awami League central leader Ivy Rahman were killed and scores hurt in Aug 21,2004 grenade attack on Awami League rally at Bangabandhu Avenue . Some 22 people stand charged in the cases, including former BNP state minister Abdus Salam Pintu, his brother Maolana Tajuddin, also the alleged grenade supplier, and Mufti Hannan, leader of banned Islamist outfit Harkat-ul-Jihad-al-Islami. bdnew
